-- EADS gives green light for A350 XWB
-- 
-- Fri Dec 1, 2006 8:17pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/12/02/businesspro-eads-350-launch-dc-idUSWEA093220061202

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - The board of European aerospace group 
EADS EAD.PA> gave the green light on Friday for the development 
of the Airbus A350, its latest design for a mid-sized jet, EADS 
said in a statement. 

  EADS did not disclose the costs of developing the A350 
extra-wide body, or "XWB," but industry analysts have estimated 
it would cost around 10 billion euros ($13.3 billion).